Netflix, Inc.

100 Winchester Cir. 
Los Gatos CA 95032 United States
Phone: +1 408-___-____
Fax: +1 408-___-____
http://www.netflix.com





233
Managers




250
IT employees




$232.9MEST.
IT Budget




Founded in 1997, Netflix, Inc. is an online movie rental subscription service operating in the United States. Subscribers have access to 100,000 DVD and Blu-ray titles from TV and film. Netflix ships these titles to subscribers using the USPS. Netflix… MoreFounded in 1997, Netflix, Inc. is an online movie rental subscription service operating in the United States. Subscribers have access to 100,000 DVD and Blu-ray titles from TV and film. Netflix ships these titles to subscribers using the USPS. Netflix operates 58 distribution centers across the US. In addition, subscribers can instantly stream content from an additional 12,000 title library directly into their homes using a range of electronic devices. This streaming service is also available in Canada, and in all of Central and South America.
Founded in 1997, Netflix, Inc. is an online movie rental subscription service operating in the United States. Subscribers have access to 100,000 DVD and Blu-ray titles from TV and film. Netflix ships these titles to subscribers using the USPS. Netflix… MoreFounded in 1997, Netflix, Inc. is an online movie rental subscription service operating in the United States. Subscribers have access to 100,000 DVD and Blu-ray titles from TV and film. Netflix ships these titles to subscribers using the USPS. Netflix operates 58 distribution centers across the US. In addition, subscribers can instantly stream content from an additional 12,000 title library directly into their homes using a range of electronic devices. This streaming service is also available in Canada and by 2012, all of Central and South America. 

IT Priorities:
• Increasing spending within the area of cloud research, in order to keep pace with startup streaming companies.
• Migrating the relational data warehousing environment from Teradata to Amazon's Redshift platform.
• Increasing spending within the company's Hadoop supported cloud data warehouse environment. 
• In the process of migrating all data in favor of Amazon Web Services and the cloud. The data center for corporate IT will be eliminated at the end of this process by the end of 2014. 
• In the process of implementing a bring your own device (BYOD) program. In regards to security, the company plans to focus on content security, not device security. They do not plan to have a mobile device management (MDM) policy. 

IT Structure:
• Internal IT is one of the many technology divisions under the Chief Product Officer. The other divisions are Cloud Operations, Content Delivery, Product Development, and eCommerce. The work of these five divisions often overlap.

IT Vendors:
• Cloud solutions is hosted by Amazon Web Services. 

IT Intelligence Snippets:

• Netflix has selected Janitor Monkey's cloud solution to assist in cleaning up unused storage space within the company's Amazon Web Services (AWS) cloud environment. 
• Partnered with big data specialist Sumo Logic, in order to analyze its customer base.
• Announced plans to offer its own content delivery network, which will help spread bandwidth burden beyond regular Internet providers.
• Selected Intequus as its systems integrator to design and manufacture its data center appliances.
• The company is completely virtualized.

Enterprise:
• The most reliable method of contact for Netflix employees is via email. The company is relying less and less on phone numbers and voice mails.





